## ğŸš¨ CRITICAL RULES

### âŒ NO CUSTOM SCRIPTS POLICY
**NEVER create standalone scripts outside the Rust codebase:**
- âŒ Shell scripts (*.sh files) - exceptions only for legacy deployment wrappers
- âŒ Python scripts (*.py files)
- âŒ Any standalone executable scripts
- âœ… ALL functionality MUST be in Rust source under `src/`
- âœ… Execute features ONLY via compiled `osvm` binary
- âœ… Use `cargo build` to compile changes
- âœ… Run via `./target/debug/osvm` or `cargo run`

**Why**: OSVM is a self-contained binary tool. All features must be compiled into the binary to maintain consistency, security, and portability.

